{{Quote|Despite all diplomacy and the handshaking and the rhetoric, to build a better [[Earth|world]] sometimes means tearing the old one down.|Alexander Pierce to [[Steve Rogers]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Secretary '''Alexander {{Conjecture|Goodwin}} Pierce''' was one of [[Hydra]]'s leaders and its top undercover operative within the {{WPS|United States government}}. Following an incident in [[Bogotá]], he lost faith in diplomacy and was recruited by Hydra. By [[1989]], he became Undersecretary of the [[World Security Council]] and arranged for [[Werner Reinhardt]]'s release from prison. Following his promotion to Secretary, he oversaw [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s operations and appointed [[Nick Fury]] as the organization's Director.

By [[2012]], he had become the leader of Hydra and made a personal visit to [[Stark Tower]] following the [[Battle of New York|Battle]] of [[New York City|New York]] in order to reacquire the [[Tesseract]] and secure [[Loki]]'s capture, although his efforts were thwarted. In [[2014]], he conspired to use [[Project Insight]] to give Hydra absolute control over [[Earth]], and with the [[Winter Soldier]] under his control, ordered the assassinations of Fury, [[Steve Rogers]] and [[Natasha Romanoff]]. During the [[Battle at the Triskelion|battle]] at the [[Triskelion]], Pierce was forced to witness as Project Insight was destroyed by the efforts of Captain America, [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] and [[Maria Hill]]. As the [[Hydra Uprising]] began, Pierce killed most of the other members of the World Security Council and attempted to kill Romanoff, although he was killed by Fury before he could succeed.

==Biography==
{{MD|Alexander Pierce (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Career===
====State Department====
{{Quote|This man declined a {{WPS|Nobel Peace Prize}}. He said peace wasn't an achievement, it was a responsibility. See, it's stuff like this that gives me trust issues.|[[Nick Fury]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Alexander Pierce was born to a father who served in the {{WPS|101st Airborne Division}} during [[World War II]].{{Ref|CATWS}} His family connections allowed him to rise up the ranks much easier than others.{{Ref|SI102}} He went on to have a niece and had at least one child, a daughter. While working for the [[United States Department of State]], a hostage situation in [[Bogotá]] caused Pierce to meet [[Nick Fury]], who successfully saved the hostages, including Pierce's daughter. Pierce had hoped to negotiate with {{WPS|National Liberation Army (Colombia)|ELN}}, but Fury disagreed. Disobeying direct orders, Fury ordered a military operation that rescued the hostages before they were to be killed. The episode in Bogotá caused a shift in Pierce's attitudes toward diplomacy, and soon after he was recruited by [[Hydra]].

Due to his achievements, Pierce was once nominated for the {{WPS|Nobel Peace Prize}}. However, Pierce declined the prize, quoting that peace was not an achievement but a responsibility. This action gained him Fury's trust.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Head of S.H.I.E.L.D.====
[[File:Pierce, A 1992.PNG|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce in the {{WPS|Joint Chiefs of Staff}} meeting]]
{{Quote|Undersecretary Pierce took pity on [[Werner Reinhardt|him]]. Said it wasn't his choice which side the of the [[World War II|war]] he was on.|[[Hauer]] to [[Rivera (S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Rivera]]|The Things We Bury}}
By the [[1980s]], Pierce held the rank of Undersecretary of the [[World Security Council]], and ordered the release of [[Werner Reinhardt]], a [[Hydra]] scientist who was sentenced to life imprisonment by [[Peggy Carter]] in [[1945]]. Reinhardt was released from the [[Rat (Facility)|Rat]] and moved by Hydra's moles in [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] to his [[Hydra Fortress|old fortress]] in [[Austria]].{{Ref|AoS208}} [[Gideon Malick]] saw the potential of Pierce, and considered having him as a partner on his quest to bring [[Hive]] back from [[Maveth]], but Malick considered Pierce to be too bloodthirsty.{{Ref|AoS309}}
[[File:Fury and Pierce.png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce awards [[Nick Fury]] for his bravery]]
In [[1992]], Pierce assisted to a {{WPS|Joint Chiefs of Staff}} meeting. After being promoted to Secretary, Pierce appointed Fury as the Director of S.H.I.E.L.D., having been impressed by Fury's actions years prior in [[Bogotá]].{{Ref|CATWS}} He also met [[Melinda May]], one of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s best agents.{{Ref|AoS119}}

====[[Battle of New York]]====
[[File:Alexander Pierce (Avengers Endgame).png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce confronts the [[Avengers]]]]
{{Quote|Alexander Pierce. He's the man above the folks behind [[Nick Fury]]."<br>"My friends call me Mr. Secretary. I'm gonna have to ask you to turn that [[Loki|prisoner]] over to me.|[[Iron Man/New York Time Heist|Tony Stark]] and [[Alexander Pierce/New York Time Heist|Alexander Pierce]]|Avengers: Endgame}}
Following the [[Battle of New York]], accompanied by several [[Hydra]] operatives posing as [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agents, Pierce headed to [[Stark Tower]] after the [[Chitauri]] were all defeated. Once there, while [[Jasper Sitwell]] and his [[STRIKE]] operatives went to retrieve [[Loki]]'s [[Scepter]] to be studied by [[List]], Pierce demanded the [[Avengers]] to hand Loki and the [[Tesseract]] over to them, especially the cube as it had been S.H.I.E.L.D.'s property since [[World War II]].
[[fILE:Alexander Pierce (May 4, 2012).png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce argues over the [[Tesseract]]]]
This led to a heated discussion with [[Thor]], who felt it necessary to take Loki and the Tesseract back to [[Asgard]], because he had to be punished by [[Odin]] due to being an [[Asgardian]] war criminal. However, Pierce refused to listen to Thor and instead demanded [[Tony Stark]] to hand over the case with the Tesseract, even attempting to grab the case when he would not comply.{{Ref|AE}} However, Pierce's attempts to secure both ended in naught, as Thor succeeded in retaining custody of the Tesseract and returned it, along with himself and Loki, to Asgard.{{Ref|TA}}

===[[Project Insight]]===
====World Security Council Meetings====
[[File:Alexander Pierce.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce talks with the [[World Security Council]]]]
{{Quote|See, I took a seat on the [[World Security Council|Council]] not because I wanted to, but because [[Nick Fury|Nick]] asked me to. Because we were both realists.|Alexander Pierce to [[Steve Rogers]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
As the Secretary of the [[World Security Council]], Pierce started to use his influence and the database that housed the mind of [[Arnim Zola]] to develop [[Project Insight]], outwardly an operation involving three heavily armed [[Helicarrier]]s and network of targeting satellites that were allegedly supposed to form a security network to protect the [[United States of America]]. In truth, [[Hydra]] actually desired to use them to target and kill approximately twenty million people selected by [[Arnim Zola]]'s algorithm, any individual which was deemed to pose a threat to Hydra's new world order.{{Ref|CATWS}} Pierce was in regular contact with [[John Garrett]] as Project Insight developed.{{Ref|AoS119}}

====Nick Fury's Interference====
[[File:AlexanderPierce1-TWS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce discusses [[Georges Batroc]]'s attack]]
{{Quote|I want you to call for a vote. [[Project Insight]] has to be delayed."<br>"Nick, that's not a favor, that's a sub-committee hearing. A long one.|[[Nick Fury]] and Alexander Pierce|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Pierce had a meeting with the [[World Security Council]] discussing the response to the hijacking of the ''[[Lemurian Star]]'' by [[Georges Batroc]]. When [[Rockwell (Councilman)|Rockwell]] suggested that the French were involved Pierce corrected him about the fact that Batroc was Algerian before discussing how this was one attack and suggested that the Council were being threatened too easily by such attacks.
[[File:Nick Fury & Alexander Pierce.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce having his meeting with [[Nick Fury]]]]
The meeting was interrupted by [[Nick Fury]] who privately asked Pierce to delay [[Project Insight]] due to Fury's need to ensure there was no risk with the operation. Pierce was at first reluctant as he noted that such a request would require a subcommittee hearing, but Fury argued that if there was a risk it would be worth the extra work. Pierce agreed as long as Fury promised to convince [[Iron Man]] visit his niece's birthday party. When Pierce learned that the [[Hijacking and Retaking of the Lemurian Star|hijacking]] of the ''[[Lemurian Star]]'' was actually planned by [[Nick Fury]] in order to recover the confidential files related to the [[Project Insight]], Pierce deployed the [[Winter Soldier]] to kill him with apparent success.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Hunting Captain America====
[[File:Alexander Pierce and Captain America.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce personally greeting [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]]]
{{Quote|[[Steve Rogers|Captain Rogers]] has information regarding the death of [[Nick Fury|Director Fury]]. He refused to share it. As difficult as this is to accept, Captain America is a fugitive from [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]|Alexander Pierce|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Following Fury's [[Attack on Nick Fury|apparent demise]], Pierce had a meeting with [[Sharon Carter]] before meeting with [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] to discuss the attack. Pierce revealed to Rogers how [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] had captured and questioned [[Georges Batroc]] and discovered from him that [[Nick Fury]] was responsible for the hijacking of the [[Lemurian Star]] and that Fury had bugged Rogers' apartment. Pierce spoke to Rogers about his own history with Fury and how a mission to rescue hostages in [[Bogotá]] had led to Fury's promotion to the head of S.H.I.E.L.D.
[[File:Pierce.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce and [[Steve Rogers]] discuss [[Nick Fury]]]]
When Rogers refused to reveal why Fury had been in his apartment the night he died, Pierce realized that Rogers was hiding something from him, likely meaning that his plans were under threat due to something Fury may have said to him. As Rogers left Pierce told him that he would find out the truth before he deployed corrupt [[STRIKE]] agents to capture Rogers, who overpowered the agents and escaped before going undercover along with [[Black Widow]].
[[File:Cap2 3099.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce makes [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] a target]]
As the attack on Rogers was seen by all of the [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] Agents inside the [[Triskelion]], Pierce called a meeting with the staff, many of whom, including [[Sharon Carter]], were questioning why Rogers had become a target. As [[Jasper Sitwell]]'s reasons were not being listened to, Pierce came down in person and revealed to the agents that Rogers was withholding information about Director [[Nick Fury|Fury]]'s death which made him an enemy of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]
[[File:APierceSpeaksToHawley.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce updates the [[World Security Council]]]]
When the [[World Security Council]] demanded an update on the situation, Pierce tried to explain himself but found his job on the line. When Rogers and Romanoff's location was given away by the use of an encoded hard drive, Pierce sent the [[STRIKE]] team to capture them, only for them to fail. They were later located in [[Camp Lehigh]], so Pierce made the call to destroy the base, with Rogers, Romanoff and the [[Hydra]] computer program housing the consciousness of [[Arnim Zola]] inside.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Briefing the Winter Soldier====
[[File:Cap2 4125.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce speaks to the [[Winter Soldier]]]]
{{Quote|The timetable has moved. Our window is limited. [[Steve Rogers|Two]] [[Black Widow|targets]], level six. They already cost me [[Arnim Zola|Zola]]. I want confirmed death in ten hours.|Alexander Pierce to [[Winter Soldier]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
When Pierce learned that [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and [[Black Widow]] had survived the explosion and escaped yet again, he gave the [[Winter Soldier]] the assignment to assassinate Rogers and Romanoff. During his conversation with the Winter Soldier, Pierce's housemaid [[Renata]] entered; knowing that no one could know about Pierce's relationship with the assassin, Pierce shot and killed Renata in cold blood.
[[File:APierceShootingRenata.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce coldly murders [[Renata]] in his home]]
Rogers was able to capture [[Jasper Sitwell]], who revealed all of Pierce's plans with [[Project Insight]]. Upon realizing Sitwell was a liability, Pierce gave a [[Battle of Washington, D.C.|second order]] for Sitwell to be killed as well. After a [[Battle of Washington, D.C.|battle]] on the streets of [[Washington, D.C.]], [[STRIKE]] teams managed to capture Rogers, Romanoff and [[Sam Wilson]], but they were soon extracted from custody by an undercover [[Maria Hill]].{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Winter Soldier's Breakdown====
[[File:AlexanderPierce-GiftToMankind.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce speaks to [[Winter Soldier]]]]
{{Quote|Your work has been a gift to mankind. You shaped the century. And I need you to do it one more time. Society's at a tipping point between order and chaos. And tomorrow morning, we're going to give it a push.|Alexander Pierce to [[Winter Soldier]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Pierce met with the [[Winter Soldier]] at the [[Ideal Federal Savings Bank]] to make him report the failures of his mission to kill [[Steve Rogers]]; however, the Winter Soldier was unstable due to seemingly remembering Rogers from a past life. When the Winter Soldier noted that he felt he knew Rogers from some long-lost memory, Pierce tried to convince him that it was simply because he had encountered him during the [[Attack on Nick Fury]], but the Winter Soldier remained unconvinced and seemed to continue questioning how he knew Rogers.
[[File:AlexanderPierce-LeaveswithRumlow.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce leaves [[Winter Soldier]] to suffer]]
When Pierce tried both beating and talking to the Winter Soldier to try to stable him and failed, he tried to reason with him by commenting on how his work as the key assassin for [[Hydra]] had helped shape mankind for the better over the years and his continued work would still help them. When this failed, Pierce ordered Winter Soldier's mind to be [[Memory Suppressing Machine|wiped]] to be ready for his next mission. He left as the Winter Soldier screamed in pain.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====[[Battle at the Triskelion]]====
[[File:World Council TWS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce with the [[World Security Council]]]]
{{Quote|What if [[Pakistan]] marched into [[Mumbai]] tomorrow, and you knew they were going to drag your daughters into a soccer stadium for execution, and you could stop it with a flick of the switch... wouldn't you?|Alexander Pierce to [[Singh]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Pierce proceeded with his plan to invite the [[World Security Council]] into the [[Triskelion]] to witness the beginning of [[Project Insight]], but as [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] prepared to deploy the Helicarriers, [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] with [[Maria Hill]] and [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] infiltrated the Triskelion and revealed by loudspeaker the truth behind [[Hydra]]'s plans and Pierce's true loyalty, and prompted every clean agent to stand up against HYDRA.
[[File:RollinsPierce-CATWS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce captures the [[World Security Council]]]]
While Rogers and Wilson infiltrated the [[Helicarrier]]s to modify their programming to change the targets from the people selected by Zola's algorithm to the Helicarriers themselves, Pierce found himself being threatened by the Council who were now prepared to stand against him. However, [[Jack Rollins]] and a [[STRIKE]] team entered the room and took the Council hostage while [[Brock Rumlow]] ensured the Helicarriers launched.
[[File:AlexanderPierce-SpeaksTo-Singh.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce tries to reason with [[Singh]]]]
Pierce tried to show Singh and the other Council members his point of view, but they refused to listen. Seeing that Singh would not stand with him, Pierce took Rollins' gun and prepared to execute him. However, [[Black Widow]] suddenly revealed she had infiltrated the Triskelion by impersonating [[Hawley]] of the World Security Council by using a [[Photostatic Veil]]. Romanoff quickly defeated STRIKE and captured Pierce.
[[File:AlexanderPierce-AreYouReady.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce mocks [[Black Widow]]'s efforts]]
With Pierce now seemingly defenseless, he watched as Romanoff began to leak all of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s files and history onto the internet for the entire world to see. However, Pierce tried to stop her by noting that if she did then her own past would also be revealed, including her violent history as an assassin. Romanoff refused to listen, and Pierce noted that she needed two high-level members to finish her plan. She explained company was coming.
[[File:Alexander-Pierce-Nick-Fury-Threat.png|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce is confronted by [[Nick Fury]]]]
Much to Pierce's surprise, the "company" turned out to be [[Nick Fury]], who had survived his [[Attack on Nick Fury|assassination attempt]]. Fury confronted Pierce about his plan and questioned why he had ever made him the head of S.H.I.E.L.D., Pierce explained it was simply because he was the most ruthless man he had ever met and was the best at his job. Pierce suggested that S.H.I.E.L.D. and Hydra did, in fact, share the same enemies and they needed the courage to take the step to destroy them, which Fury refused to do.
[[File:AlexanderPierce-EyeScan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce is forced to assist [[Nick Fury]]]]
Pierce was forced by Black Widow to help her and Fury to unlock every single one of S.H.I.E.L.D./Hydra's secrets and upload them to the Internet. Although Pierce mocked their efforts as he claimed that Fury's password had been deleted, Fury revealed that he was still able to use his blind eye under his eyepatch to unlock the system and complete their plan, much to Pierce's disdain as he watched the intel begin trending online.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Destruction of Project Insight====
[[File:AlexanderPierce-Kills-Council.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce executes all of the Council Members]]
{{Quote|You know, there was a time I would have taken a bullet for you."<br>"You already did. You will again when it's useful.|[[Nick Fury]] and Alexander Pierce|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
With his plans in ruins and all of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s and [[Hydra]]'s secrets released to the world, Pierce made a desperate attempt for freedom and executed the [[World Security Council]] members, except for [[Black Widow]], by detonating a [[Explosive Security Badges|miniature bomb]] that he had given to them disguised as an access chip. He then ordered Romanoff and [[Nick Fury]] to lay down their weapons and allow him to escape to the helicopter.
[[File:AlexanderPierce-WhatAWaste.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce watches [[Project Insight]]'s failure]]
As Pierce watched from the window, he witnessed [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s plans succeed as the [[Project Insight]] Helicarriers began firing upon each other, destroying them before they could unleash their planned massacre. Pierce used the threat of the bomb on Black Widow's clothes to force Fury to let him go. As he was leaving, Fury informed him that he would have once taken a bullet for Pierce; in response, Pierce jokingly threatened that Fury would again.
[[File:Cap2 1080p 6986.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Pierce is shot and killed by [[Nick Fury]]]]
Refusing to allow such a dangerous enemy to escape, Romanoff used a [[Taser Disk]] to short out the bomb and knock herself unconscious, leaving Pierce momentarily shocked and defenseless. This gave Fury the opportunity to fatally shoot Pierce twice in the chest, knocking him back through a glass wall. Pierce uttered "Hail Hydra," and died laying in a pile of broken glass and his own blood, moments before [[Helicarrier|Helicarrier IN-01]] destroyed the [[Triskelion]].{{Ref|CATWS}}
{{Clear}}

===Legacy===
====Hydra's Exposure====
{{Quote|You're afraid it was Alexander Pierce."<br>"Secretary Pierce was the man in charge... the only person [[Nick Fury|Fury]] took orders from, and he was [[Hydra]].|[[Maria Hill]] and [[Melinda May]]|Nothing Personal}}
Following the [[Battle at the Triskelion]], the death of Pierce, as well as the destruction of the [[Triskelion]] and the reveal of all of [[Hydra]]'s secrets to the public, was reported to [[Baron Strucker]] by [[List]] on the [[Hydra Research Base]] at [[Sokovia]]. However, von Strucker assured List that it was not Hydra's end, and they had the [[Scepter]] to [[War on Hydra|counterattack]] [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and the [[Avengers]].{{Ref|CATWS}}

A news report confirmed Pierce's death too, describing him as a particular individual who seemed to have been involved instrumental in orchestrating the Battle at the Triskelion, causing [[Brock Rumlow]] to defect from Hydra and become an independent terrorist.{{Ref|CACWPIC}} In [[2016]], Pierce was called "one of the most controversial figures of our time" by [[WHiH World News]].{{Ref|WNF201}}

==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Avengers: Endgame. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|Diplomacy? A holding action, Nick. A band-aid. And you know where I learned that. [[Bogotá]]. You didn't ask, you just did what had to be done. I can bring order to the lives of seven billion people by sacrificing twenty million. It's the next step, Nick, if you have the courage to take it.|Alexander Pierce to [[Nick Fury]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
*'''Master Tactician''': Pierce was a very skilled tactician. As a politician, he made very important decisions for [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] as well as against it. He orchestrated [[Hydra]]'s [[Hydra Uprising|Uprising]]. This included controlling the [[Winter Soldier]] to make assassinations on people who are a threat to Hydra, like President [[John F. Kennedy]]. He also planned some of [[Project Insight]]. In preparation for this, he had three [[Helicarrier]]s built and even convinced [[Nick Fury]] for a short while. He also tried to convince [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] to think Fury was the enemy. He took control of the [[World Security Council]] before he was stopped by Fury and [[Black Widow]].
*'''Master Spy''': Pierce used his great abilities as a spy to infiltrate the [[World Security Council]], [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], and the United States Government, all while ensuring that the only people who knew about it were within [[Hydra]].
*'''Marksman''': Pierce was skilled in the use of firearms, particularly pistols. He shot and killed [[Renata]] and later threatened the [[World Security Council]] with his sidearm.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''{{WPS|SIG Sauer P226}}''': [[File:Pierce Kills Renata.png|thumb|250px|Pierce shooting and murdering [[Renata]]]] Pierce used this pistol to shoot and kill his housemaid [[Renata]].
*'''{{WPS|Glock|Glock 19}}''': Pierce used this pistol to threaten the members of the [[World Security Council]].

===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|Unless you want a two-inch hole in your sternum, I'd put that gun down. That was armed the moment you pinned it on.|Alexander Pierce to [[Black Widow]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
*'''[[Explosive Security Badges]]''': Pierce had used these miniature explosives, disguised as security badges, to kill [[World Security Council]] members [[Singh]], [[Yen]], and [[Rockwell (Councilman)|Rockwell]], and attempted to use it to kill [[Black Widow]].

==Facilities==
*'''[[Alexander Pierce's Residence]]''': Pierce used his residence in [[Washington, D.C.]] to run his operations out of. The [[Winter Soldier]] went to the house one night to receive a new mission, when the [[Renata|housemaid]] saw them talking, forcing Pierce to shoot her.
*'''[[Triskelion]]''': [[File:Cap2 1425.jpg|thumb|250px|Pierce inside the [[Triskelion]]]] As the member of [[World Security Council]] and the Undersecretary of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], Pierce had his own office at the S.H.I.E.L.D. headquarters in [[Washington, D.C.]] Possessing the [[Zola's Algorithm|algorithm]] from [[Arnim Zola]], Pierce started the [[Project Insight]] at the Triskelion in order to eliminate the most dangerous targets for [[Hydra]]. Before the launch of the Project, Pierce invited the fellow councilmen to the Triskelion, however, [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] exposed that S.H.I.E.L.D. was compromised by Hydra led by Pierce. Pierce threatened to kill the councilmen before he was stopped by [[Black Widow]] who intended to expose the Hydra conspiracy. As [[Nick Fury]] suddenly appeared in front of Pierce, he killed the councilmen and attempted to leave the Triskelion with Romanoff, however, was killed by Fury.
*'''[[Ideal Federal Savings Bank]]''': [[File:Cap2 5299.jpg|thumb|250px|Pierce visiting the [[Winter Soldier]]]] Pierce used [[Hydra]] assets to establish the secret compound in [[Washington, D.C.]] beneath the abandoned bank building where he kept the [[Winter Soldier]]. Following the [[Battle of Washington, D.C.]], Pierce visited the Winter Soldier at the compound, demanding the report about the incident. As Pierce figured that he started remembering [[Steve Rogers]] and his former life, he ordered scientists to wipe out the Winter Soldier's memory with [[Memory Suppressing Machine]].

