==Trivia==
*In the comics, Alexander Pierce is a [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] field agent and the leader of one of the three teams of [[Caterpillars]].
**The MCU version is an amalgamation of the character with '''Aleksander Lukin''', the [[Winter Soldier]]'s handler.
*Pierce is shown to have {{WPS|Newman's Own}} spaghetti sauce in his refrigerator. This is a reference to Robert Redford famously working with {{WPS|Paul Newman}}.
* Pierce mentions his father served in the {{WPS|101st Airborne Division}} during [[World War II]]. Robert Redford portrayed WWII paratrooper {{WPS|Julian Cook}} in the 1977 film ''{{WPS|A Bridge Too Far (film)|A Bridge Too Far}}'', albeit of the {{WPS|82nd Airborne Division}}.

==Behind the Scenes== 
*Alexander Pierce in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the second live-action incarnation of the character, following an incarnation portrayed by {{WPS|Neil Roberts (actor)|Neil Roberts}}.
*[[Robert Redford]] was cast as Alexander Pierce partly as an homage to his roles in [[1970s]] thrillers such as ''{{WPS|Three Days of the Condor}}''.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130529233200/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/05/02/iron-man-3-marvel-phase-two/3/ 'Iron Man 3' kicks off Marvel's Phase Two: New images and revelations in build-up to 'Avengers 2' -- EXCLUSIVE]</ref> [[Anthony Russo|Anthony]] and [[Joe Russo]] described Redford as "''an acting legend playing a villainous role''" akin to {{WPS|Henry Fonda}} in ''{{WPS|Once Upon a Time in the West}}''.{{Ref|CATWSAC}}
*{{WPS|Alec Baldwin}} was considered for the role of Alexander Pierce but turned down due to his wife's pregnancy at the time.<ref>[https://www.mtv.com/news/t73fsg/alec-baldwin-marvel-movie-villain Alec Baldwin Was Almost A Marvel Movie Villain]</ref>

